@Node 3 "Usage"

 The best way to use LockupV4.3 is by using @{" LockupTools " link 9}.

 Just double click on the LockupTools43 icon in the LT drawer and
 LockupTools will give you easy access to LockWB, EDL-U & EDL-M.

 @{fg shine}How To Use LockupV4.3:-@{fg text}

 The best way to use Lockup is to @{" install " link 5} it.  If you want to test Lockup
 first then Double Click on the @{fg shine}SetAssign@{fg text} Icon.

 When you have installed Lockup their are 3 ways you can use Lockup:-

 1. Double click on the icon. ( L4.3 ).
 2. Open Shell and type @{fg shine}Lockup:LockupV4.3@{fg text}
 3. Double click on the @{fg shine}LockWB@{fg text} icon in the @{fg shine}end-s/@{fg text} drawer.

           @{fg fill}-----------------------------------------------------@{fg text}

 If you use option 3 then you will be able to select which screen you want
 Lockup to use.

 If everything is ok you should see this @{" window ", link "Lo.IFF/MAIN"}.
 This is Lockup's window, which you will see every time you bootup.

 Since this is the first time you have used the program you will not have
 setup any other users.  To get back to before you ran the program you
 must enter a username and password.

 User Name:- @{fg shine}main.a@{fg text}
  Password:- @{fg shine}password@{fg text}

 If you have created more than one user you can use any one you want.
 E.G. if you created new username called @{fg shine}ab.c@{fg text} and the password was @{fg shine}cool@{fg text}.
 Then you would enter the username @{fg shine}ab.c@{fg text} with the password @{fg shine}cool@{fg text}, and you
 would get back to before we ran Lockup

 @{" Snapshot The Window              " link 32}
 @{" Change Protection Window Picture " link 101}

 @{" Lockup's Main Window " link 31}
 @{" Contents             " link main}

@endnode

@node 31 "Lockup's Main Window"

 The window contains 3 gadgets:-

 1. @{fg shine}About@{fg text} - Press this button to display infomation about the program.

 2. @{fg shine}User Name@{fg text} - This string gadget is selected when the program starts.
                Enter you user name in here and press Return.  When you
                press return the Password gadget is selected.

 3. @{fg shine}Password@{fg text}- Enter your password here and press Return.

 NOTE: When you type the password all you will see is @{fg shine}***@{fg text} instead of
       letters.  This is so that people can't see your password.
       See @{" Thanks " link 11} for more information.

 If you get both the User Name and Password correct then the window will
 close and you will be able to access Workbench.

 If is the first time of using the program then:-

 user name will be:- @{fg shine}main.a @{fg text}

 password will be:- @{fg shine}password @{fg text}

 @{" Previous " link 3}
 @{" Contents " link Main}

@ENDNODE

