@node users "Edit Lockup Password - Users"

 @{fg shine}Please Note@{fg text}:- The password must not have spaces and is limited to 49
               letters.

 How a user can edit his/her password:-

 Double click on the @{fg shine}ELP-U@{fg text} icon. in the edp-u drawer

 A window will apper with the current user name in the 'User Name' gadget
 and the 'Old Password' gadget will be selected.

 Type in your old password and press return.  Then the 'New Password' gadget
 will be selected.  So type in a new password and press return.

 Press @{fg shine}Save@{fg text} to save the new password.  If you get the old password wrong
 then an error message will apper.

 Press @{fg shine}Help@{fg text} for some help.
 Press @{fg shine}Cancel@{fg text} to use the old password.

 @{" Contents " link Main}
 @{" Previous " link 3}

@ENDNODE

@node muo "Edit Lockup Password - Main User"

 @{fg shine}NOTE:-@{fg text} This program can only be used by the main user.

 To use the program Double Click on the @{fg shine}ELP-M@{fg text} icon.
 in the edp-m drawer

 A window will apper asking you to enter the main user password.  Do so and
 press return.  If you are not the main user press Cancel.

 If you get it correct the window will close and another window will apper.
 If you get it wrong the program will exit and return you to Workbench.

 Note: If you have not edited the main users password then the main users
 password is @{fg shine}password@{fg text}.

                @{fg shine}---------------------------------------------@{fg text}

 The window is made up of 2 parts:-
 1. The Users panel ( the top box ).
 2. The Main panel ( thr bottom box).

 @{fg shine}The Users Panel:- @{fg text}

 This panel is used to create username with passwords or edit exsiting
 username passwords.

 @{fg shine}3 Easy Steps to creating a new username with password.@{fg text}

 1. Click in User Name gadget with the mouse and enter a username.
    - This can be anything you want, but I recomend you use your initials
      with a dot then a letter. eg @{"fg shine}sk.a@{"fg text}.

 2. Click in the Password gadget with the mouse and enter a password for
    that user to use.
    - This password can be changed with @{" EditLockupPassword-Users " link users} later.

 3. Press Save to save the username and password.

 More help can be obtained by pressing the @{fg shine}Help@{fg text} button in the User Panel.

 @{" User Panel in detail " link userp}


 @{fg shine}The Main Panel:-@{fg text}

 This panel is used to edit the main user password.

 @{fg shine}How to edit the main user password@{fg text}

 1. Click in the Password gadget in the main panel and delete what it
    contains.

 2. Type in a new password.

 3. Press Save

 The password will then be saved.

 @{fg shine}NOTE:-@{fg text} If you forget this password you will NOT be able to use ELP-M.
        It is a good idea to write this password down.  Remember to keep
        this password safe.  This pasword is used by the username @{fg shine}main.a@{fg text}
 
 @{" Main Panel in detail" link userm}

 @{" Contents            " link main}

@endnode 

@node userp "User Panel"

 @{fg shine}User Panel@{fg text}

 This panel is the top half of the window with 2 string gadgets and 3 button
 gadgets.

 @{fg shine}User Name@{fg text} - String gadget - This is where you enter a new user name or you
                             see the current user name in memory.  eg sk.a
                             For your user names I suggest you use the users
                             initials of there names - If your name was
                             Paul Ben Taylor then his user name would be
                             pbt.a

 @{fg shine}Password@{fg text} - String gadget - This is where you enter a new password for a new
                            user or edit the current users password in
                            memory.  It must not have any spaces in it and
                            is limited to 49 letters.

 @{fg shine}Load@{fg text} - Button - When you press this, a file requester will apper asking you
                 to select a user to load.  Pick one.  Note that main.a
                 can`t be loaded.  The file will be loaded and the User Name
                 gadget will be changed to the file you loaded.  Also the
                 password from the file will apper in the Password Gadget.

 @{fg shine}Save@{fg text} - Button - Save the current user file.

 @{fg shine}Help@{fg text} - Button - Displays some help on how to edit/create files.

 @{" Back " link muo}

@endnode

@node userm "Main Panel"

 @{fg shine}The Main Panel @{fg text}

 This is the bottom half of the window, and has 1 string gadget and 1
 button gadget. It also shows the main Users name which is @{fg shine}main.a@{fg text}

 @{fg shine}Password@{fg text} - String Gadget - This shows the main users password, and allows
                            you to edit it.  Please not the password must
                            not have any spaces in it and is limited to 49
                            letters.

 @{fg shine}Save@{fg text} - Button - This save the password in the Password gadget to the main
                 users file.

 Note that if you forget this password you can't use ELP-M.

 @{" Back " link muo}

@endnode

@Node 5 "Installing Lockup"

 To install Lockup double click on the @{fg shine}Install_Lockup@{fg text} icon.

 Follow the commands given by the installer program and select where to
 install Lockup.

 NOTE The install script does not create a drawer for Lockup.  You have to
      do this before running the installer.

 This program also adds lines to the user-startup in the S: drawer.  This
 means that the next time you boot your hard drive Lockup will apper.

 If you have Lockup V 4.2 double click on the @{fg shine}Update_Lockup@{fg text} icon.

